Interface IEditData

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    DialogEditPerson

    public interface IEditData
    Interface provides basic functionality to work with custom data classes.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      java.lang.Object createData()
      Creates new data.
      java.lang.Object createRandomData()
      Creates random data.
      boolean editData(java.lang.Object paData)
      Opens an editor and let user edit data given as parameter.
      void inspectData(java.lang.Object paData)
      Opens an editor in READ ONLY mode.

    • Method Detail

      • createData

        java.lang.Object createData()
        Creates new data. This method should invoke an editor to fill properties.
        Returns:
        new data instance.

      • createRandomData

        java.lang.Object createRandomData()
        Creates random data. Does not invoke an editor, instead fills up the attribues with meaningful values. This method is used in structures testing.
        Returns:
        new data instance randomly initialized.

      • editData

        boolean editData(java.lang.Object paData)
        Opens an editor and let user edit data given as parameter.
        Parameters:
        paData - instance of data to modify.
        Returns:
        true, if data was mdified (user pressed OK) false otherwise (Cancel).

      • inspectData

        void inspectData(java.lang.Object paData)
        Opens an editor in READ ONLY mode. User can inspect fields of data.
        Parameters:
        paData - instance of data to inspect.
